---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
---
<Layout title="Systems Impact" description="13.3× KV-cache compression (measured) and 4–8× FLOP savings (projected) from HeadGenome routing.">
<div class="page-top">
  <p class="eyebrow">04 — Systems Impact</p>
  <h1>The taxonomy makes<br/>attention cheaper.</h1>
  <p class="lead">
    By routing each head through a mask matched to its functional class, we achieve
    13.3× KV-cache compression on Llama-3.2-1B (directly measured) and project
    4–8× FLOP reduction at long context.
  </p>
</div>

<div class="section">

  <div class="honesty-note reveal">
    <p>
      <strong>Measured vs. projected.</strong> We distinguish these carefully throughout.
      KV-cache compression was measured on hardware. FLOP savings are FLOP-model projections
      from measured head fractions — exact under a sparse kernel backend, not wall-clock timings.
    </p>
  </div>

  <hr/>

  <h2 class="reveal">KV-Cache Eviction <span class="badge badge-measured">Measured</span></h2>
  <p class="reveal">
    Local and Sink heads do not need full KV-cache history. By evicting all but the sliding
    window (Local) or a fixed token budget (Sink), we reduce KV-cache memory footprint by
    13.3× on Llama-3.2-1B. Retrieval and Induction heads retain their full cache.
  </p>

  <div class="systems-row reveal">
    <div class="sys-cell">
      <span class="badge badge-measured">Measured</span>
      <div class="sys-num">13.3×</div>
      <div class="sys-desc">KV-cache compression on Llama-3.2-1B</div>
    </div>
    <div class="sys-cell">
      <span class="badge badge-measured">Measured</span>
      <div class="sys-num">~85%</div>
      <div class="sys-desc">of heads use local or sink routing — no full KV needed</div>
    </div>
    <div class="sys-cell">
      <span class="badge badge-projected">Projected</span>
      <div class="sys-num">4–8×</div>
      <div class="sys-desc">FLOP reduction at N=4K–32K context</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <hr/>

  <h2 class="reveal">Projected Speedup Curves <span class="badge badge-projected">Projected</span></h2>
  <p class="reveal">
    The FLOP model uses empirically measured head-type fractions. Local heads cost O(N·W);
    critical heads (Retrieval + Induction) cost O(N²). The speedup grows monotonically with
    context length and converges to the critical-head ceiling = 1/f_critical.
  </p>

  <div class="formula reveal">
    Speedup(N) = N² / [ f<sub>crit</sub>·N² + f<sub>local</sub>·N·W ]
    → 1/f<sub>crit</sub> as N→∞
  </div>

  <div class="reveal">
    <table class="data-table">
      <thead>
        <tr><th>Model</th><th>f_critical</th><th>Ceiling</th><th>@ N=4K</th><th>@ N=32K</th></tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td>GPT-2 Medium</td><td>15%</td><td>6.7×</td><td>3.9×</td><td>6.1×</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Qwen-0.5B</td><td>12%</td><td>8.3×</td><td>4.4×</td><td>7.7×</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Llama-3.2-1B</td><td>15%</td><td>6.7×</td><td>3.9×</td><td>6.1×</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Qwen-1.5B</td><td>14%</td><td>7.1×</td><td>4.0×</td><td>6.5×</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <figure class="figure reveal">
    <img src={`${base}/figures/fig11_speedup.png`} alt="Speedup curves" loading="lazy" />
    <figcaption>Projected speedup curves vs. sequence length. Each architecture saturates at its critical-head ceiling.</figcaption>
  </figure>

  <div class="callout warn reveal">
    FLOP projections follow the methodology of StreamingLLM, H2O, SnapKV, and MagicPIG.
    They are exact under FlexAttention or a custom sparse CUDA kernel.
    The current PyTorch-mask reference backend adds overhead rather than reducing it.
  </div>
</div>
</Layout>

<style>
.section { max-width:820px; margin:0 auto; padding:3rem 2.5rem 8rem; }
.section h2 { font-size:clamp(1.5rem,3vw,2.2rem); font-weight:200; letter-spacing:-.04em; line-height:1.15; margin-bottom:1.25rem; display:flex; align-items:center; gap:.75rem; flex-wrap:wrap; }
.section p { color:var(--text-2); font-weight:300; line-height:1.75; margin-bottom:1rem; }
.honesty-note {
  border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: var(--radius-sm);
  padding: 1.5rem 2rem; background: var(--bg2);
  font-size: .9rem; color: var(--text-2); font-weight: 300; line-height: 1.65;
}
.honesty-note strong { font-weight: 500; color: var(--text); }
.systems-row {
  display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(180px,1fr));
  gap: 1px; background: var(--border); border-radius: var(--radius);
  overflow: hidden; margin: 2.5rem 0;
}
.sys-cell {
  background: var(--bg); padding: 2.5rem 2rem;
  display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: .6rem;
}
[data-theme="dark"] .sys-cell { background: var(--bg2); }
.sys-num {
  font-size: 2.8rem; font-weight: 200; letter-spacing: -.06em;
  font-family: var(--font); color: var(--text); line-height: 1;
}
.sys-desc { font-size: .82rem; color: var(--text-3); font-weight: 300; line-height: 1.4; }
.formula {
  background: var(--bg2); border-radius: var(--radius-sm); border: 1px solid var(--border);
  padding: 1.5rem 2rem; font-family: var(--mono); font-size: .85rem;
  color: var(--text-2); line-height: 2; margin: 2rem 0;
}
</style>
